main event: A UFO sighting occurred in Minneapolis, Minnesota on April 19, 1956, observed for five hours.
interesting points: The object was observed through binoculars and appeared about the size of a quarter as seen from a distance,The object emitted a high-intensity light near its bottom center,The sighting occurred at an azimuth of 290 degrees and at an elevation of approximately 35 degrees, Venus was present in the same position as the UFO at the time of observation, The report concluded that the sighting was likely caused by Venus or another celestial phenomenon.
sighted object: one stationary object emitting high-intensity light
